  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***concession*** is the writer's acknowledgment that an opposing point has merit. It is the complement of [counterargument](./counterargument.md): where a counterargument is the opposing position itself, a concession is the writer's admission that the opposing position has force.",
  "name": "Concession",
